---
description: Frontend standards for Next.js, shadcn, Tailwind, and PWA
globs: apps/web/**/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx,mjs}
alwaysApply: false
---

# Web Standards (`apps/web`)

- Use App Router patterns and keep route components focused on UI composition.
- Build UI with shadcn primitives first; keep styling token-driven via Tailwind variables.
- Prefer server components by default; use client components only when state/effects are required.
- Keep pages lightweight; extract reusable logic into `src/lib` or feature-level modules.

# PWA and Build Constraints

- Keep `next-pwa` compatibility with Next.js 16 by using webpack mode where required.
- Do not manually edit generated `public/sw.js` or `public/workbox-*.js`.
- Ensure `manifest` metadata stays aligned with product branding and installability.

# Data Access

- Validate request/response data with Zod at API boundaries.
- Use typed clients and avoid duplicating API contract shapes manually.
